cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.GT, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category as it deals with resource allocation in cellular networks. It may also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it involves optimizing the allocation of resources. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it involves managing and controlling the allocation of resources. It may also be relevant to cs.GT (Game Theory) as it uses utility functions to allocate resources fairly. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia) as it considers different types of traffic, including real-time applications.
